  output: # Custom window aggregations

Use this when the workbook already contains a neighboring formula that demonstrates the intended date, datetime, or workday window and the task asks you to extend that same logic to new rows or columns.

```python
from openpyxl import load_workbook

wb = load_workbook("input.xlsx")
ws = wb["Sheet1"]

anchor = ws["A2"].value
lower = f'=WORKDAY({anchor.coordinate},-4)'
ws["C2"] = (
    '=SUMIFS($B$2:$B$100,$A$2:$A$100,">"&WORKDAY(A2,-4),'
    '$A$2:$A$100,"<="&A2)'
)
…(truncated)

